Main Thesis: There are two types of pessimisms in the discursive tradition: psychological pessimism and transcendental pessimism. 
 + These types of pessimisms are distinct in kind.
 + Transcendental pessimism is philosophical in kind.
 + Psychological pessimism is not philosophical in kind.
 - We should only adhere to the standards and framework of transcendental pessimism when we attempt pessimistic arguments in philosophical practice.
